    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Such a switch, if implemented, would be at the trait/mod level rather than something user facing.\r\n\r\nTS (and i'm sure the later games) repathed to avoid cliff blockers, so not implementing this would be a gameplay bug in addition to being annoying.  The AI would benefit from the actor blocker detection in all mods.\r\n\r\nI suspect that TS used the same criteria as for visibility, so that gives us an even easier height check that *could* be done before firing."
